HEADWORD: Microcyte
<hw>Mi"cro*cyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ a hollow vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>One of the
elementary granules found in blood. They are much smaller than an
ordinary corpuscle, and are particularly noticeable in disease, as in
anaemia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

